# pr-view-valid.json.meta — provenance sidecar (#347 W1c2, #398).
#
# Canonical `gh pr view --json <fields>` payload shape carrying the full W1c1
# vocabulary — the runner drives `chp_pr_view` with various FIELDS_CSV subsets
# to prove:
#
#   - normalized-shape projection: EXACTLY the requested fields appear in
#     stdout; unrequested vocabulary fields are ABSENT (not silently promoted).
#   - `comments` normalizes to `[{id,author,body,createdAt}]` ascending by
#     createdAt (fixture is intentionally OUT-OF-ORDER to prove the leaf sorts).
#   - `reviews` normalizes to `[{author,state,submittedAt}]` ascending by
#     submittedAt (fixture out-of-order likewise).
#   - `closingIssueNumbers` folds `closingIssuesReferences.nodes[].number` to
#     an int array (the GitHub-internal cursor shape does NOT cross the seam).
#   - `body: null` normalizes to `""` per the vocabulary.
#   - Fail-CLOSED: gh-stub failure → verb rc≠0 with no partial stdout.
